<br>
Hippolyte never once turned her back on Alysia. Even when Aly came to Themiscrya an ex Roman, it was Hippolyte who took her in, trained her, it was Hippolyte that was there when Alysia claimed Scynthia. And it was Hippolyte who stood at her side when they organized the Amazon Nation Alliance.<br>
<br>
Though the Scynthian had been away from the Nation for a time now, she felt Hippolyte's presence back in battle, and she'd never allow her athelfi to fight alone.<br>
<br>
She appeared stepping through the woods, right in front of them. She came barefoot and wearing her amazon leathers which compared to most Northern tribes, left little to the imagination. Two large white wolves stood at either side of their Queen. Scythe and Aeceus. Alysia smiled to Hippolyte and bowed to a knee speaking the word &quot;Vasilissa&quot;. And both wolves bowed their heads before Hippolyte as well.<br>
<br>
Alysia rose and smiled to her old friend. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 751<br> <font color=#993300>(2/15/03 11:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=24>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gathering of the Amazons</span><hr size=1> Hippolyte caught the bow and arrows as they were tossed to her.  It was no surprise at all the weapons that the assassin pulled out of her &quot;bag&quot;.  Dawn was skilled in them all.  <br>
<br>
Cassandra watched and then answered Lysia, &quot;Just men...I mean they look like Roman men I suppose.&quot;<br>
<br>
Then in walked Alysia with her trusted companions.  Hippolyte smiled and saluted her athelfi.  &quot;Seems Artemis's arrows are awakening the souls of many amazons to our calling.&quot;  She grinned at Alysia.  Hippolyte knew Alysia too felt something happening.  The shamanic nature of the Scythians was well known.<br>
<br>
&quot;This is a village of men...Roman men.  From what Cassandra and Kara have told me...they kidnapped their ..so called &quot;wives&quot;.  Building a town between here and Troy.  But, what they didn't know... is the land is just on this side of the Amazon Nation.  Our land....and as these women are captive.....as amazons..we owe them a chance for freedom.  To taste what we taste...by the blessings of our Gods and Ancients.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;It will be simple...as we did in the past...we will make them fear these woods.  For the wild beasts that live here..do not take a liking to them and their ways.  We will don the masks of our animals....well at least some of us.&quot;  She nodded to Dawn.  &quot;We will work at night...freeing the women...slowely..one by one.   In effect...the &quot;beasts&quot; will take their women...and &quot;eat&quot; the men.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cassandra and Kara suddenly came clue to how the old stories were made.  The wild beasts from childhood...were actually Amazons.  Amazons who freed the women from oppressive villages.<br>
<br>
 <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

Once a Vasilissa...now only a priestess and warrior of war....she wanders the amazon nation and lands of the Greeks searching the future for the past....until the day shame is no longer hers...and she can take her place in history ..once again. 
