<br>
 Grabbing a few spare logs, she tossed them into the fire, not giving it a chance to die down. Dawn knew all to well that the forest in amazon territory was freightening to those whom had never been there, and she wanted to make Cassandra and her sister's stay.. a bit more comfortable to say the least.<br>
<br>
 Dawn settled on the ground before the fire, crossing her twin scabbards across her lap, she folded her arms and hands over them. Sitting comfortably indian style, the amazon fell into a trance, her emerald pools settled on the fire. The only meditation Dawn ever did, was this, before fights, battle, war, she concentrated, focused, and saw what no one else would see. She scryed.<br>
<br>
 As Dawn fell into her thoughts, and the future, she seemed only to waver in the light of the day, and the fire. Pupil's became canine like, and teeth become feline like. Soon, she would be so in touch with her soul, her entire being that shapeshifting would come as a blur to all those around her, and her fighting would truly become the gift those had always been awed by. The gift that had made her a legend. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#993300>(2/16/03 9:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preperation.</span><hr size=1> Lysia accepted the fronds, and nodded.  &quot;An excellent plan... we'll be done in no time.&quot;  She grinned down at her queen, a far more mature one than she'd had as that earnest teenager. <br>
