She walked over to where she set down her small pouch. She reached in and pulled out two small viles. One, was a red liquid and she opened it, drizzling the liquid on the blade of one dagger. The poisoned appeared as blood. But it was deadly to no extent.<br>
The other vile, she slipped into a small pouch attached to her leather skirt. It was Wolves Blood. The healing remedy that she had discovered many years back in Scynthia. It had been know to heal the most outrageous wounds and infections.<br>
<br>
She then took a seat near the fire where her green orbs stared into the flames. A hint of blue reflected in her eyes, Alysia would always have two sides of her. Aly was her peace. Her inner beauty and love. But the warrior inside was Samsara. Samsara knew no such thing as mercy towards an enemy. They were prey, nothing more to her.<br>
The the fire light her medallions glowed brightly. One Tretmolec, one Scynthian, and one Loire.<br>
<br>
She was ready. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
